\begin_layout Subsection
Linux Notes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Linux is the preferred platform for running gvSIG.
 It offers superior 32 bit memory management and full control over the Java
 environment in which gvSIG runs.
 Linux is also our primary development and testing platform.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This software has minimal dependencies on system libraries and should run
 well on any Linux distribution that's not more than ca.
 5 years old.
 To be precise, the minimum version of GNU Libc required is 2.3.
 That version is found e.g.
 in Ubuntu 6.06.
 On Linux distributions that do not fullfill the requirements, there will
 be no raster and projection functionality.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
32 Bit compatibility libraries needed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
